    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Lend-Lease Administrator</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Secretary</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Early</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">August 11,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Proposed Release on Creation of Joint War Aid
                    Committee, U.S.–Canada</p>
                <p>The proposed release contained in Lauchlin Currie’s memorandum to the President
                    of August 3<note n="1" xml:id="d342fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> enclosed with your letter<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d342fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_657">p.
                            657</ref>, fn. 1.</note> is entirely satisfactory to Lend-Lease.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
